UID:Ysk5PzXb_YAWc61x5cf6L
SUMMARY:Neil deGrasse Tyson 2-Day Pass
DTSTAMP:20260308T063047Z
DTSTART:20260507T023000Z
DESCRIPTION:New lecture titles never before presented in Seattle: May 5th -
	 "This Just In: Latest Discoveries in the Universe" - The title says it al
	l. Drawn from within the previous two or three years of cosmic discovery -
	 with topics hand-picked for their impact on science and on the public's f
	ascinating with this moving frontier. May 6th - "Science as a Way of Knowi
	ng" - The anatomy of science: What it is. How it works. Why it works. And 
	why it's the most successful means of decoding nature that has ever been d
	evised. Learn further what social\, cultural\, and political forces stimul
	ate or thwart this moving frontier\, and what this bodes for the future of
	 nations and our species.\nMetal detectors & bag search at door. Arrive ea
	rly. No weapons. www.stgpresents.org/about/safety The Paramount Theatre is
	 located in downtown Seattle at 911 Pine Street\, Seattle\, WA 98101. Ther
	e is an overall 8 ticket limit per patron. Patrons exceeding the ticket li
	mit will have their orders canceled at the venue's discretion. All sales a
	re final. No refunds or exchanges. Mobile barcodes delayed until 4 days pr
	ior to event. Venue reserves the right to change delivery methods. Unless 
	otherwise noted\, each person must have a ticket regardless of age. No bab
	ies in arms. When purchasing ADA accessible seating\, please feel free to 
	contact us by email if assistance is needed with accommodations or compani
	on seating\; you may reach us at accessibility@stgpresents.org. Each acces
	sible seat houses an armless freestanding chair for patrons with mobility 
	impairments and their companions. Please note that our historic theatre ha
	s no elevator to the balcony levels.\n\nhttps://www.ticketmaster.com/neil-
	degrasse-tyson-2day-pass-seattle-washington-05-06-2026/event/0F00632CC69B3
	2D1\n\nFrom STG - Paramount Theatre
